' plan-59-E: CONVERTED from `resource-non-owner-return-invalid`.
'
' Used to assert a `RES` parameter could not be RETURNed
' (`TYPE_RESOURCE_INVALIDATE_NOT_OWNER`, retired). Returning the pointer hands it
' to the caller, whose scope becomes the outermost one touching the resource, so
' it is closed exactly once — there.
'
' Kept rather than deleted so the original intent stays traceable; only the
' verdict changed.
IMPORT fs

' plan-52-A row 10: `RETURN` of a non-owning parameter is rejected. This is the
' rule the whole STATE model rests on: a bare parameter may forget the state its
' argument carries (§15.5) ONLY because that pointer cannot outlive the frame it
' was passed to. If it could escape, the opaque reading would leak a resource
' whose state type nobody agrees on.
'
' Its sibling resource-invalidate-not-owner-invalid pins the close case;
' this one pins the escape.
FUNC steal(RES p AS File) AS RES File
  RETURN p
END FUNC

FUNC main AS Integer
  RES f AS File = fs::openFile("tests/syntax/resources/resource-non-owner-return-valid/src/main.mfb")
  RES g AS File = steal(f)
  fs::close(g)
  RETURN 0
END FUNC
